<br>
I hate the flagging system. I can see them locking some of the zones to make getting to them very hard. Just seems they didn't put enough experience zones in for the lvl 65 non-uber crowd. The quest to get to most of the tier 3 zones are very hard, and once you get there getting a group is near impossible.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>THE GOOD</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Sun Vortex<br>
<br>
Can't say enough about this spell. In terms of nukes it is by far the best one in the mage spell book. Finally having a upgrade to shock of fiery blades is really sweet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Fire Bolt of Tallon<br>
<br>
Still one of the spells I keep memed at all times. When you need something to die NOW it truly comes in handy.<br>
<br>
Servant of Marr<br>
<br>
The best pet in the expansion. It can't tank at all but it does very good damage. 85dps is nothing to sneeze at. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Talisman of Return<br>
<br>
I use this spell so much. It is probably one of my favorite spells in the expansion. A very great utility spell, and has come in handy so many times for me.  Finally a summoned item with a nice effect. The component cost needs to be lowed to around 55p instead of the 110p it cost but aside from that it is a great utility spell.<br>
<br>
Suspend Menion<br>
<br>
I can't imagine life without it. It is one of the first PoP aa skills I purchased, and althought not mage only is probably the best PoP skill we get. Makes pet canni in groups very easy. Cast time should be instant though.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>THE OK</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Black Steel <br>
<br>
This is a nice spell but really not all that great. The resist rate on this spell in PoP seems on the high side. The damage is still rather low, and is pretty worthless in trials due to the high magic resistance of mobs.<br>
<br>
Sun Storm<br>
<br>
Another ok spell. Really only suitable over Fire Bolt of Tallon if aggro is a issue. Even with full debuffs the resist rate on rains over all is still way to high. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Belt of the Magikot<br>
<br>
Two hp belts in 5 levels seems like a waste.  Guess they ran out of ideas..........<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>THE BAD</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Servant of Ro<br>
<br>
This aa is worthless. I advise anyone with a brain to never waste time on this skill.  There are way better ones to get, and since this pretty much does nothing vs. PoP mobs it falls into the Frenzy Burnout category.<br>
<br>
Rathe's Son<br>
<br>
This pet is so crappy considering it was a lvl 65 spell which is uber hard to get.   The damage is insanely low, and the low damage mitigate makes it worthless.<br>
<br>
Child of Ro<br>
<br>
Do I really have to go into details why this pet sucks? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Elemental Silence<br>
<br>
WHY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!<br>
<br>
Anyway that is pretty much my take on the PoP aa abilities, and spells available to mages.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
